  <bioghist id="aspace_53e7e3a8ebddedf95d83ef55c5cbe4b2">
    <head>ORGANIZATIONAL HISTORY</head>
<p>1% for Peace was founded in Ithaca (N.Y.) with direct assistance from Ben and Jerry's Ice Cream to promote the direction of 1% of the Defense Dept. budget to social causes. In January 1992, the group changed its name to Business Partnership for Peace and clarified its mission as a lobbying group for an alternative approach to national security issues. In 1993 the group officially merged with Businesses for Social Responsibility and moved its operations to Washington, DC.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_f3e8022e4055f4991403d974dcec5db9">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Correspondence, records, subject files, financial and organizational records, records pertaining to the founding of 1% for Peace, letters received and queries, and ephemera.</p>  </scopecontent>
